<item>
            <title>[LU-6317] LFSCK 4: namespace LFSCK counts the objects repeatedly</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6317</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;That is because the namespace LFSCK uses object-table based iteration plus namespace based directory traversing to scan the system. So one object may be returned twice by them.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
